<h2>Introduction:</h2>
This lab exercises the ability to:
<ul>
    <li>Use predefined JavaScript Functions to solve problems.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Lab Assignment:</h2>

<ol>
    <li> Create a new directory, <b><tt>Lab4</tt></b>, in your class account directory.</li>
    <li> Move into your <tt>Lab4</tt> directory</li>
    <li> Using a <span style="color:fuchsia"><b><u><i>syntax-highlighting</i></u></b></span> editor,
	 open a new file to edit.  Save it as <tt><i>filename</i>.html</tt>.</li>
    <li> For each of the following programming exercises:</li>
    <ol>
	<li> modify your Web page file via the editor</li>
	<li> save the file</li>
	<li> refresh the browser open to your Web page</li>
	<li> verify that your modifications did what you've intended</li>
	<li> Use HTML comments at the top of each file identifying:</li>
	<ol>
	    <li>where the file is located (e.g. <tt>~/cs200999/labs/Lab4/<i>filename</i>.html</tt>)</li> 
	    <li>the author (<i>you</i>) </li> 
	    <li>what the program does</li> 
	    <li>when you created the file</li> 
	    <li>when you last modified the file</li>
	</ol>
    </ol>
</ol>
Perform <i>all</i> of the requirements in each of the following Exercises in Reed:
<ol>
    <li> <u>Exercise 5.8</u> </li>
    <li> <u>Exercise 5.10</u> </li>
    <li> <u>Exercise 5.14</u> </li>
</ol>
    <p>
    When finished (after you’ve tested and proofread each of your Web pages), submit your <b>three</b> sets of files to the appropriate D2L dropbox.
